<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="1463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1463">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.55/34.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-14">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 14, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Panaman Government has at last moment withdrawn clause conveying
                            ultimatum and reopened negotiations. No arrests made and period of ten
                            days granted to allow further consideration by the Chinese of
                            Government’s altered requirements with regard to application of Law 50.
                            Panaman Government offers upon registration the issuance of a new and
                            more satisfactory cédula confirming acquired rights of Chinese.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wicker</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>